<refentry>
  <refnamediv id="avgAggregate">
    <refname>avg</refname>

    <refpurpose>Average (mean) aggregate</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>AQL% <command>SELECT</command> avg(<replaceable>attribute</replaceable>) <command>FROM</command> <replaceable>array</replaceable>;</synopsis>

    <synopsis>AFL% aggregate(<replaceable>array</replaceable>,avg(<replaceable>attribute</replaceable>)<optional>,<replaceable>dimension_1</replaceable>,<replaceable>dimension_2</replaceable>,...</optional></synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Summary</title>

    <para><indexterm>
        <primary>average</primary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>aggregates</primary>

        <secondary>avg</secondary>
      </indexterm>The avg aggregate takes a set of scalar values from an array
    attribute and returns the average of those values.</para>

    <para>The average of an empty set is NULL. The avg of a set that contains
    only NULL values is also NULL. If the set contains NULL and NOT NULL
    values, the avg result is an average of the NOT NULL values only.</para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Example</title>

    <informalexample>
      <para>This example finds the average of every column of a 3<symbol
      role="symbolfont">×</symbol>3 matrix.</para>

      <procedure>
        <step>
          <para>Create a matrix m3x3:<programlisting>CREATE ARRAY m3x3&lt;val:double&gt;[i=0:2,3,0,j=0:2,3,0];</programlisting></para>
        </step>

        <step>
          <para>Put values of 0–8 into m3x3:<programlisting>store(build(m3x3,i*3+j),m3x3);</programlisting><screen>[
[(0),(1),(2)],
[(3),(4),(5)],
[(6),(7),(8)]
]</screen></para>
        </step>

        <step>
          <para>Find the average of every column of m3x3:<programlisting>aggregate(m3x3,val,j)</programlisting>This
          query returns:<screen>[(3),(4),(5)]</screen></para>
        </step>
      </procedure>
    </informalexample>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
